nl_problem:
# Task: permutations_with_duplicates
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: permuteUnique(self, arg1)

Given a collection of numbers, nums, that might contain duplicates, return all possible unique permutations in any order.

Constraints:
- 1 <= nums.length <= 8
- -10 <= nums[i] <= 10
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "permuteUnique")
  (signature ( (self Solution) (nums list int) ) (list list int))
  (constraints
    (constraint "1 <= nums.length <= 8")
    (constraint "-10 <= nums[i] <= 10")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return all possible unique permutations in any order.")
    (rule "The permutations should be unique, even if the input contains duplicates.")
    (return "A list of lists, where each sublist is a unique permutation of the input numbers.")
  )
)
